,"topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q04","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"\\[23, \\quad 17, \\quad 11, \\quad 5, \\quad \\ldots\\]\n\n(a) \nt Write down the next number in this sequence.\n\nt Find the $n$th term of this sequence.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q05","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":5,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q05","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Factorise completely.\n\\[8g - 2g^2\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q06","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":6,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q06","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"**Without using a calculator**, work out $\\displaystyle\\frac{4}{7} \\div 8$.\n\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q07","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":7,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q07","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Solve.\n\n(a) \nt $15t + 8 = 4 - t$\n\nt $\\displaystyle\\frac{25 - 2u}{3} = 2$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q08","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.8","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Standard form","qtype":"standard form","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q08","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Calculate $0.3^2$.\n\nGive your answer in standard form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q09","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":9,"marks":3,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q09","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Solve the simultaneous equations.\n\nYou must show all your working.\n\\begin{align*}\n3x - 2y &= 19 \\\\\nx + y &= 3\n\\end{align*}\n\n$x = $ \n\n$y = $","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q10","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":10,"marks":3,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry"],"s":"3.6","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Parallel lines","qtype":"parallel lines","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q10","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"In the diagram, $AB$ and $CD$ are parallel.\n\nThe lines $CB$ and $AD$ intersect at $X$.\n\n$AB = 3.0$\\,cm, $AX = 2.0$\\,cm, $BX = 2.7$\\,cm and $CD = 7.5$\\,cm.\n\nFind the length of $BC$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q11","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":11,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q11","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Find the highest common factor (HCF) of $12x^{12}$ and $16x^{16}$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q12","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":12,"marks":3,"topics":["Number","Geometry"],"s":"1.11","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Ratio and proportion","qtype":"ratio and proportion","g":"proportion","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q12","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"In a regular polygon, the interior angle and the exterior angle are in the ratio interior : exterior $= 11 : 1$.\n\nFind the number of sides of this regular polygon.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q13","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":13,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.12","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Rates","qtype":"rates","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q13","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"The diagram shows the speed--time graph for part of a car journey.\n\nCalculate the total distance travelled during the 10 seconds.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q14","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":14,"marks":3,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"3.4","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Length and midpoint","qtype":"length and midpoint","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q14","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"The diagram shows a sector of a circle with centre $O$ and radius 9\\,cm.\n\nThe length of the chord $PQ$ is 6\\,cm.\n\nCalculate the length of the arc $PQ$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q15","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":15,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q15","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Simplify $\\left(3125w^{3125}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{5}}$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q16","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":16,"marks":3,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.8","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Proportion","qtype":"proportion","g":"proportion","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q16","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"$y$ is inversely proportional to $x^2$.\n\nWhen $x = 3$, $y = 2$.\n\nFind $y$ when $x = 2$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q17","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":17,"marks":6,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"3.2","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Drawing linear graphs","qtype":"drawing linear graphs","g":"graph","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q17","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"$ABCD$ is a cyclic quadrilateral, $ABX$ is a straight line and $PQ$ is a tangent to the circle at $A$.\n\nAngle $CBX = 85°$, angle $BAQ = 55°$ and angle $CAD = 42°$.\n\nFind\n\n(a) \nt angle $CBD$\n\nt angle $ACB$\n\nt angle $ADC$\n\nt angle $BCD$\n\nt angle $PAD$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q18","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":18,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.4","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Similarity and congruence","qtype":"similarity and congruence","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q18","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Two solids are mathematically similar and have volumes 81\\,cm$^3$ and 24\\,cm$^3$.\n\nThe surface area of the smaller solid is 44\\,cm$^2$.\n\nCalculate the surface area of the larger solid.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q19","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":19,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q19","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Find the values of $x$ when $6x + y = 10$ and $y = x^2 - 3x + 10$.\n\n{---}]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q20","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnum":20,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/22/M/23 Q20","year":2023,"session":"March","tex":"Find the $n$th term of each sequence.\n\n(a) \nt $-1, \\quad 0, \\quad 7, \\quad 26, \\quad 63, \\quad \\ldots$\n\nt $24, \\quad 12, \\quad 6, \\quad 3, \\quad 1.5, \\quad \\ldots$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2023March-Paper22-Q21","paper":"2023March-Paper22","qnu